DIV3.P:
“Now abating a few Fractions, which, in dividing Persons,
cannot be exactly observed, it is plain, 30 to 400 is very near
what 6000 l. is to 70000 l, as follows;

“Thus, tho, the Scots, by this Union, paid but 48000l. for
Scotland to 1997000 l. English, which was about 1/40 part,
forthy times 48000 l. being 1920000 l. to have argued
from thence, That they should have but 13 Members,
which, to the House of Commons, is 1/39 6/13 part of 513;
This would appear ridiculous.

